Jul 28 2009 	Good Value Option	I stayed at Edward II with my husband and my brother and sister in law. We stayed in a room with two queen beds.The building is in a good location: it is around 10 to 15 minutes by bus from Union Square; it is a five-minute walk to the famous Union St Shops, it is a five-minute walk to the wonderful restaurants of Chestnut Street, and it is within walking distance to the Presidio. Fisherman's wharf, where Alcatraz cruises depart from, requires two buses.The building itself is old but attractive. The interior is by no means &quot;modern&quot; - it still has many original fixtures and fittings - however our room was very clean and had enough space for luggage for four people. The room was made up each day with fresh towels and the beds were made. We had to ask twice for toilet paper though.The breakfast is plain and simple with no cooked food. There is a fresh fruit basket, Cheerios, Raisin Bran, muffins, fruit toast, English muffins, plain bread, orange juice, milk and water. My only complaint is that out of five nights at Edward II, we only got two breakfasts, because the breakfast only starts at 8am and if you have a day trip (e.g. Alcatraz, Napa Wine tour) you need to leave earlier than 8am. Also, there wasn't enough space for everyone to sit on the mornings we did have breakfast.All in all this is a very cheap option and I have no major complaints. I think personally it is probably important to remember that this is a budget option (for example, my husband + his siblings are staying in a hostel at the moment and we are &quot;budget travellers&quot;). It is a very small fraction (perhaps a quarter) of the cost of the downtown options and so, to me at least, it seems logical that you should have proportionate expectations. In summary, I would recommend staying here if you are a budget traveller with realistic expectations about what to expect in terms of value in a world-famous city in a great location. If you would like all the frills I would not recommend staying here and I would suggest paying the extra to go somewhere else, as this property will definitely not meet the expectations of everyone.	
