Apr 6 2009 	Quaint basic B	My husband and I stayed at Edward II when we were in town for two nights for a wedding. We booked at the last minute and there was availability when most other hotels were occupied for a big convention in town. The room was a little bit on the shabby side, but it was very charming and clean enough, as was the whole hotel. The big reason to stay here is the location. It is very conveniently located right off Chestnut Street in the Marina district and close to the water. Each morning we strolled the 10 minutes to the waterfront to watch the joggers and look at the Golden Gate Bridge. Breakfast was simple but tasty. Another plus, we were able to check in late at night after a long drive. Overall, I thought it was a good value for San Francisco, which is a very expensive city, and I would stay here again. If you are looking for a reasonably priced place to stay in the Marina District, and you like &quot;shabby chic&quot; b&amp;bs with personality, give this place a shot. If you're looking for stylish, modern, immaculate, try someplace else.	
